"{\"uid\": \"breitbart.com-entertainment-2024-07-27-meet-the-french-theater-director-behind-the-olympics-drag-queens-same-sex-foreplay-queer-last-supper-opening-ceremony\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The 2024 Summer Olympic Games in Paris kicked off Friday with an opening ceremony that left many stunned and repulsed - drag queens cavorting in the streets, raunchy same-sex foreplay, and a gender-queer re-enactment of The Last Supper.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 236, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 33, \"end\": 38, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999708962, \"rank\": 2.930770378761643e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was even a bearded \\\"woman\\\" crawling around on all fours in a provocative blue bustier.\", \"from\": 238, \"to\": 330, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Who was responsible for the unfolding artistic atrocity?\", \"from\": 332, \"to\": 388, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meet Thomas Jolly, a theater and opera director who was little-known outside of France before Friday's broadcast - which was viewed by more than a billion people worldwide - turned him into a global curiosity.\", \"from\": 389, \"to\": 598, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 394, \"end\": 400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.9953049899944103, \"rank\": 0.003620262932061364, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}, {\"begin\": 469, \"end\": 475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9527642585871744, \"rank\": 0.04950646200028752, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In interviews prior to Friday's broadcast, the openly gay Thomas Jolly gave no indication that he would be turning the Opening Ceremony into a Pride parade.\", \"from\": 600, \"to\": 756, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 658, \"end\": 664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.9953049899944103, \"rank\": 0.003620262932061364, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}, {\"begin\": 719, \"end\": 735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9967961495529207, \"rank\": 0.00272539523229659, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But he did emphasize the importance of inclusion and representation.\", \"from\": 757, \"to\": 825, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"How do you write a show in which everybody, at one point, feels represented and a part this bigger thing, this bigger 'us'?\\\"\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 952, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"he said.\", \"from\": 953, \"to\": 961, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's ambitious but also complex because one has to broaden one's own imagery, one's own outlook and include everyone, understand everyone so that no one feels left behind.\\\"\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 1135, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For a family friendly event, Olympic organizers provided no advance warning of the sheer number of drag queens and gender non-conforming performers who would be on display, nor did they mention the ceremony's bizarrely horny undercurrents, with performers engaging in simulated acts of lust.\", \"from\": 1137, \"to\": 1428, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They certainly gave no clue about The Last Supper parody, which prompted a swift backlash among Christians - many of whom noted that Jolly would not have dared to mock Islam in the same fashion.\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1624, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1526, \"end\": 1536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9786765031399131, \"rank\": 0.012972900313907914, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the \\u00a0tableau vivant, Jesus Christ is played by an obese woman wearing a dress with plunging cleavage.\", \"from\": 1626, \"to\": 1730, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1650, \"end\": 1662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999233905357, \"rank\": 7.660935598673621e-08, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 1679, \"end\": 1684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Obesity\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2845894146993554e-18, \"text\": \"obese\", \"types\": [\"Q12136\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Obesity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Obesity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The disciples are played mostly by drag queens in brightly colored wigs.\", \"from\": 1731, \"to\": 1803, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly, 42, has been heralded as a wonder boy of the French theater, infusing the classics with post-modernism and avant-garde provocations.\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 1944, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1857, \"end\": 1871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Theatre_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9999999986971488, \"rank\": 1.0276411562448355e-09, \"text\": \"French theater\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Theatre_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Theatre_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has directed for some of France's most prestigious institutions including the Paris Opera and the Festival d'Avignon.\", \"from\": 1945, \"to\": 2065, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1973, \"end\": 1979, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9527642585871744, \"rank\": 0.04950646200028752, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2026, \"end\": 2037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_Opera\", \"score\": 0.9999998819807913, \"rank\": 1.1411027558766774e-07, \"text\": \"Paris Opera\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_Opera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_Opera\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His taste for the outr\\u00e9 clearly informed his choices for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2067, \"to\": 2137, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Friday's spectacle included what appeared to be a male performer with one of his testicles hanging visibly outside his lady undergarment.\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2276, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There was also an actress playing a decapitated Marie Antoinette, with her severed head singing the French Revolution anthem\\u00a0\\\"\\u00c7a ira.\\\"\", \"from\": 2278, \"to\": 2412, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2326, \"end\": 2342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.748455482403283e-29, \"text\": \"Marie Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"https://twitter.com/vision4theblind/status/1816925182319104013?s=46&t=JFbLGFjrj_iZzQdm7CUOlw  Follow David Ng on Twitter@HeyItsDavidNg.\", \"from\": 2414, \"to\": 2549, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Have a tip?\", \"from\": 2550, \"to\": 2561, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Contact me atdng@breitbart.com  Pleaselet us knowif you are having issues with commenting.\", \"from\": 2562, \"to\": 2652, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2025 Breitbart\", \"from\": 2662, \"to\": 2688, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2679, \"end\": 2688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breitbart_News\", \"score\": 0.9999999999349711, \"rank\": 6.502652632739503e-11, \"text\": \"Breitbart\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breitbart_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breitbart_News\"}]}]}"